CatDescriptText: This branch of the Carnegie Library moved to 419 Dinwiddie St. in 1982, the original site is now a religious institution.  This band has three female majorettes and an all male group of musicians, most wearing dark uniform jackets.  The instruments shown in the image include trombone, tuba, flute, clarinet, saxophone, snare drum, bass drum, and cymbals.
TitMainTitle: Iron City Elks Lodge No. 17 Band on the steps of Carnegie Library of Pittsburgh, Wylie Avenue Branch
